{
  "texts": [
    "It is also noticeable that the SSD case has larger divergence values despite the higher resolution.",
    "The case with the stronger magnetization but more regular field has smaller divergence.",
    "Given the complexity of these realistic simulations, compared to the case of the RTI, we consider these values acceptable.",
    "Splitting variables into equilibrium and perturbation parts stems from the very origin of the MANCHA3D code to study wave propagation in the solar atmosphere (Khomenko and Collados, 2006; Felipe, Khomenko, and Collados, 2010).",
    "It allows preserving potentially large contrast between oscillating and background quantities with a good numerical accuracy."
  ]
}